result.execSummary:
The defendant Catherine F. Figahs was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Issue of Worthless Checks(<=$2500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.24(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Restitution in the amount of $48.76 paid directly to the Clerk of Court's Office prior to sentencing.  The 10% surcharge in the amount of $4.88 still due and owing - same repayment conditions apply as noted below for the Costs.

Cash Bond previously posted in the amount of $228.00 and Restitution overpayment has been applied.  The remaining balance of the Costs in the amount of $199.88 is to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.    Complete ID process with the Sheriff's Department.

Case Called @ 10:36AM: Defendant Catherine F. Figahs in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Resolution recited by DA.  Recommendation for simple costs w/full payment of Restitution.  Def confirms resolution.    Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: NC   Court accepts plea and enters JOC.   Statement by Def:  Yes.  The Court:  Notes full Rest has been PIF of $48.76 - balance of overpayment to be applied against the Court Costs with DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.  Appeal Rights Given.  Must Complete ID process and DNA with WCSD.

Pre-trial conference on June 1, 2016 at 11:30 am.
Plea/sentencing hearing on June 14, 2016 at 11:00 am.

Defendant is prohibited from issuing any checks for payment or maintaining an open checking account.  She is not prohibited from using her debit card however.  Defendant may issue a check for her monthly rent payment, however no other issuance of checks for payment.  The issue of the ID process with the Sheriff's Department will be held in abeyance pending appearance for the Plea and Sentencing.

Case Called @ 2:25 PM: Defendant Catherine F. Figahs in court, appearing via telephone by prior approval by the Court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def does not wish counsel today.  NGP received and entered.   PTC.STC Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for June 1, 2016 at 11:30 am.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for June 14, 2016 at 11:00 am.
